This code demonstrates passing and returning strings in ONC RPC.

Compile it with:
SunOS:	make
OS X:	make -f Makefile.linux
Linux:	make -f Makefile.linux

Before compiling, be sure that you edit strings.x and
change the XXXXX in the program number to some numbers
of your choice.

Start the server on one machine (e.g. remus)

	$ ./server

Run the client:

	./client <localhost> <teststring>
for example:
	./client remus this is a test

and get the results.
